id: agent_eval
definitions:
  targetNamespace: http://bpmn.io/schema/bpmn
  xmlns:bpmn: http://www.omg.org/spec/BPMN/20100524/MODEL
  xmlns:studyflow: http://behaverse.org/schemas/studyflow/v1
  xmlns:cognitive: http://behaverse.org/schemas/studyflow/cognitive
  xmlns:exec: https://w3id.org/studyflow/exec
  xmlns:agentic: https://w3id.org/studyflow/agentic
  xmlns:functional: https://w3id.org/studyflow/functional
Agent_Eval:
  type: bpmn:Process
  documentation: |
    An agent-evaluation harness: for every item in an eval set, run a tool-using
    agent, check its output, score it, and collect the results - with a sample
    routed to human raters, and the whole eval wrapped in a loop that refits the
    agent's instructions until the score clears the bar.

    The point of the diagram is the line down the middle of it. Everything outside
    the Agent follows a path the diagram fixes: fan out, guard, judge, collect.
    Inside the Agent, nothing does - the model picks which tool to call and when,
    and stops when it decides it is done. That is the difference between a workflow
    and an agent, and here it is the difference between a plain sub-process and an
    ad-hoc one, which is the element BPMN has always used to mean "order decided at
    run time".

    Three consequences follow from drawing it this way:

    - The agent's tools are the activities inside it. A tool that is not drawn is a
      capability nobody reviewed.
    - Every step is one call the engine makes - a model request, a tool
      function, a judge - with its data arriving over the wires.
    - The eval is also the fitness function. The outer loop refits the agent's
      instructions - a plain service task bound to `python://dspy.MIPROv2`, whose
      trainable is a Prompt artifact - from each round's scores, so "evaluate the
      agent" and "improve the agent" are the same diagram.
  extensionElements:
    - type: studyflow:Study
  name: Agent evaluation harness
  flowElements:
    Start:
      type: bpmn:StartEvent
      name: Start eval
      outgoing:
        - Flow_Start_Improve
    Eval_Set:
      type: bpmn:DataStoreReference
      extensionElements:
        - type: studyflow:Dataset
      name: Eval set
    Rubric:
      type: bpmn:DataObjectReference
      extensionElements:
        - type: agentic:Prompt
          template: |
            Score the answer 1-5 on: factual support from the retrieved passages,
            completeness against the question, and absence of unsupported claims.
            A 5 requires every claim to be traceable to a passage.
      name: Scoring rubric
    Agent_Prompt:
      type: bpmn:DataObjectReference
      documentation: |
        The agent's instructions as an artifact - the trainable of this flow.
        The first wording is written by hand; each optimizer round overwrites
        it with a better one.
      extensionElements:
        - type: agentic:Prompt
          template: |
            Answer the question using the corpus. Search before you answer, cite
            the passages you used, and say so plainly when the corpus does not
            support an answer.
      name: Agent instructions
    Improve:
      type: bpmn:SubProcess
      documentation: |
        The fitting loop: evaluate the agent, and while the mean judge score is
        under the bar, refit its instructions from the scored items and evaluate
        again - BPMN's own `loopCondition` keeps the loop running while the eval
        is under the bar, and `loopMaximum` caps it at three compiles. Nothing
        about the eval changes when it is used to improve the thing it measures.
      name: Eval-optimize loop
      incoming:
        - Flow_Start_Improve
      outgoing:
        - Flow_Improve_Done
      loopCharacteristics:
        type: bpmn:StandardLoopCharacteristics
        loopCondition: mean_judge_score < 4
        loopMaximum: 3
      flowElements:
        Optimize_Prompt:
          type: bpmn:ServiceTask
          documentation: |
            The fitting step: last round's scored items are the trainset, the
            judge's score is the objective, and the agent's instructions are
            the trainable - `MIPROv2(metric, num_trials,
            max_bootstrapped_demos)` compiling the wired Prompt. On the first
            turn there are no scores yet, so the optimizer passes the
            hand-written prompt through and the baseline gets evaluated first.
          name: Optimize prompt
          outgoing:
            - Flow_Optimize_Each
          dataInputAssociations:
            Wire_Prompt_In:
              sourceRef:
                - Agent_Prompt
          dataOutputAssociations:
            Wire_Prompt_Out:
              targetRef: Agent_Prompt
          isDataOperation: true
          with:
            metric: judge_score
            num_trials: 30
            max_bootstrapped_demos: 4
          implementation: python://dspy.MIPROv2
        Per_Item:
          type: bpmn:SubProcess
          documentation: |
            One instance per item of the eval set, with the current item bound
            as `question`. The instances are independent, so this is also the
            unit of parallelism.
          name: For each eval item
          incoming:
            - Flow_Optimize_Each
          outgoing:
            - Flow_Each_Agreement
          loopCharacteristics:
            type: bpmn:MultiInstanceLoopCharacteristics
          iterate: items
          over: items
          itemVar: question
          collect: concat
          collectAs: scores
          flowElements:
            Research_Agent:
              type: bpmn:AdHocSubProcess
              documentation: |
                An ad-hoc sub-process: the model chooses which of the tools below to call,
                and how many times, until it can answer. `deterministic` is pinned false -
                the engine records each choice rather than assuming it can re-derive it.

                The instructions are wired in from the Agent instructions element by a
                plain data association - so the agent always runs whatever version the
                optimizer last wrote, and the dependency is a line on the diagram.
              extensionElements:
                - type: agentic:Agent
                  model: claude-opus-4-8
                  systemPrompt: "{{Agent_Prompt}}"
                  maxTurns: 8
              name: Research agent
              outgoing:
                - Flow_Agent_Check
              dataInputAssociations:
                Wire_Prompt_Agent:
                  sourceRef:
                    - Agent_Prompt
              flowElements:
                Search:
                  type: bpmn:ServiceTask
                  extensionElements:
                    - type: agentic:Tool
                      kind: search
                      purpose: |
                        Look up background facts. Use it when the question needs
                        knowledge you do not already have.
                  name: Search Wikipedia
                  with:
                    results: 8
                  implementation: python://wikipedia.search
                Compute:
                  type: bpmn:ServiceTask
                  extensionElements:
                    - type: agentic:Tool
                      kind: code
                      purpose: |
                        Evaluate a pandas expression over the trial table to check a
                        claim numerically. Use it when the question turns on a statistic.
                  name: Run analysis
                  implementation: python://pandas.eval
              completionCondition: answer is not null
            Check_Output:
              type: bpmn:ServiceTask
              documentation: |
                A model checks the answer before it is scored: every claim must
                be supported by a retrieved passage. A guardrail is an ordinary
                model call with a strict prompt, not a special element.
              extensionElements:
                - type: agentic:LLMCall
                  model: claude-haiku-4-5
                  prompt: |
                    Check the answer against the retrieved passages. Every claim
                    must be supported by one; reject answers that cite passages
                    the retriever never returned. Reply `pass` or `fail: <why>`.
              name: Groundedness check
              incoming:
                - Flow_Agent_Check
              outgoing:
                - Flow_Check_Score
            Score:
              type: bpmn:ServiceTask
              documentation: |
                The judge model is named on the diagram: it is part of the
                measuring instrument, and swapping it moves the numbers.
              extensionElements:
                - type: agentic:LLMCall
                  model: claude-opus-4-8
                  prompt: |
                    Apply the scoring rubric ({{Rubric}}). Give the score 1-5 and
                    one sentence of justification naming the deciding criterion.
                    Reply as `score: <n>` on the first line.
              name: Judge answer
              incoming:
                - Flow_Check_Score
              outgoing:
                - Flow_Score_Sample
            Sample:
              type: bpmn:ExclusiveGateway
              extensionElements:
                - type: cognitive:RandomGateway
              name: Sample for human review?
              incoming:
                - Flow_Score_Sample
              outgoing:
                - Flow_Sample_Human
                - Flow_Sample_Done
            Human_Rating:
              type: bpmn:UserTask
              documentation: |
                The human half of the evaluation. Two raters per sampled item, so
                agreement between them - and between them and the model judge - is
                computable rather than assumed.
              extensionElements:
                - type: agentic:HumanApproval
                  question: |
                    Rate this answer against the rubric.
              name: Human rating
              incoming:
                - Flow_Sample_Human
              outgoing:
                - Flow_Human_Done
              with:
                rubric: |
                  Score the answer against the same rubric the model judge used.
                scale: 1-5 Likert
                raters: 2
            Item_Done:
              type: bpmn:EndEvent
              name: Item scored
              incoming:
                - Flow_Sample_Done
                - Flow_Human_Done
            Flow_Agent_Check:
              type: bpmn:SequenceFlow
              sourceRef: Research_Agent
              targetRef: Check_Output
            Flow_Check_Score:
              type: bpmn:SequenceFlow
              sourceRef: Check_Output
              targetRef: Score
            Flow_Score_Sample:
              type: bpmn:SequenceFlow
              sourceRef: Score
              targetRef: Sample
            Flow_Sample_Human:
              type: bpmn:SequenceFlow
              name: sampled
              sourceRef: Sample
              targetRef: Human_Rating
            Flow_Sample_Done:
              type: bpmn:SequenceFlow
              name: not sampled
              sourceRef: Sample
              targetRef: Item_Done
            Flow_Human_Done:
              type: bpmn:SequenceFlow
              sourceRef: Human_Rating
              targetRef: Item_Done
        Agreement:
          type: bpmn:ServiceTask
          documentation: |
            Reduces the collected per-item scores to the round's mean judge
            score - the objective the optimizer maximizes and the loop
            condition reads.
          name: Score the eval
          incoming:
            - Flow_Each_Agreement
          isDataOperation: true
          implementation: python://numpy.mean
        Flow_Optimize_Each:
          type: bpmn:SequenceFlow
          sourceRef: Optimize_Prompt
          targetRef: Per_Item
        Flow_Each_Agreement:
          type: bpmn:SequenceFlow
          sourceRef: Per_Item
          targetRef: Agreement
    Done:
      type: bpmn:EndEvent
      name: Eval complete
      incoming:
        - Flow_Improve_Done
    Flow_Start_Improve:
      type: bpmn:SequenceFlow
      sourceRef: Start
      targetRef: Improve
    Flow_Improve_Done:
      type: bpmn:SequenceFlow
      sourceRef: Improve
      targetRef: Done
